  "Description": "The TPM8837C is a high-voltage H-bridge driver designed to control inductive loads such as DC motors, solenoids, and relays. It provides bidirectional drive capability with a maximum output current of 1 A from a motor supply voltage (VM) ranging from 2.5 V to 17 V. The device features a PWM control interface (IN1/IN2) compatible with 1.8-V, 3.3-V, and 5-V logic levels and includes integrated protection features like undervoltage lockout (UVLO), over-current protection (OCP), and thermal shutdown (TSD) to enhance system reliability.",
